Description: The third edition of the International Classification of Diseases for Oncology, published in 2000 used principally in tumor and cancer registries for coding the site (topography) and the histology (morphology) of neoplasms. The study of the structure of the cells and their arrangement to constitute tissues and, finally, the association among these to form organs. In pathology, the microscopic process of identifying normal and abnormal morphologic characteristics in tissues, by employing various cytochemical and immunocytochemical stains. A system of numbered categories for representation of data.
Numeric value to express the degree of abnormality of cancer cells, a measure of differentiation and aggressiveness.
Valid Values: G1 G2 G3 G4 GX GB High Grade Intermediate Grade Low Grade unknown Not Reported Not Applicable

Description: The text term used to describe the extent of metastatic disease present at diagnosis.

Description: Text term to identify an anatomic site in which metastatic disease involvement is found.
Valid Values: Abdomen Adrenal Gland Ascites Bone Bone Marrow Brain Cerebrospinal Fluid Central Nervous System Colon Distant Nodes Distant Organ Groin Kidney Liver Lung Lymph Node Axillary Inguinal Lymph Node NOS Mediastinum Omentum Ovary Pelvis Peritoneal Cavity Peritoneum Pleura Scalp Skin Small Intestine Soft Tissue Spinal Cord unknown Not Reported

Description: Text term used to describe the patient's first symptom experienced prior to diagnosis and thought to be related to the disease.
Valid Values: Altered Mental Status Headaches Motor or Movement Changes Seizures Sensory Changes Visual Changes unknown Not Reported

Description: Number of days between the date used for index and the date the patient was diagnosed with the malignant disease. If not applicable please enter 'Not Applicable'
The percentage of tumor cells spread locally in a malignant neoplasm through infiltration or destruction of adjacent tissue.
Text terms to describe the status of a tissue margin following surgical resection.
Valid Values: R0 R1 R2 RX unknown Not Reported

Description: A yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether the patient had an additional malignant diagnosis at the same time the tumor used for sequencing was diagnosed. If both tumors were sequenced, both tumors would have synchronous malignancies.
Valid Values: yes no unknown Not Reported

Attribute: Tumor Confined to Organ of Origin
Description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether the tumor is confined to the organ where it originated and did not spread to a proximal or distant location within the body.
Valid Values: yes no unknown Not Reported

Description: The text term used to describe whether the patient's disease originated in a single location or multiple locations.
Valid Values: Multifocal Unifocal unknown Not Reported

Description: Numeric value used to describe the maximum diameter or dimension of the primary tumor, measured in centimeters.
Numeric value used to describe the gross pathologic tumor weight, measured in grams.
The number that describes the distance, in millimeters, between the upper layer of the epidermis and the deepest point of tumor penetration.
The yes/no indicator to ask if large vessel or venous invasion was detected by surgery or presence in a tumor specimen.
Valid Values: Yes - Vascular Invasion Present no unknown Not Reported Not Allowed To Collect

Description: Text term that represents the type of vascular tumor invasion.
Valid Values: Extramural Intramural Macro Micro No Vascular Invasion unknown Not Reported

Description: Yes/no/unknown/Not Reported indicator used to describe whether anaplasia was present at the time of diagnosis.
Valid Values: Yes - Anaplasia Present no unknown Not Reported

Description: The text term used to describe the morphologic findings indicating the presence of a malignant cellular infiltrate characterized by the presence of large pleomorphic cells, necrosis, and high mitotic activity in a tissue sample.
Valid Values: Absent Diffuse Equivocal Focal Present Sclerosis unknown Not Reported

Description: For tumors in paired organs, designates the side on which the cancer originates.
Valid Values: Bilateral Left Midline Right Unilateral unknown Not Reported

Description: A yes/no indicator to ask if perineural invasion or infiltration of tumor or cancer is present.
Valid Values: yes no unknown Not Reported

Description: A yes/no indicator to ask if small or thin-walled vessel invasion is present, indicating lymphatic involvement
Valid Values: yes no unknown Not Reported

Description: The number of lymph nodes involved with disease as determined by pathologic examination.
The number of lymph nodes tested to determine whether lymph nodes were involved with disease as determined by a pathologic examination.
The text term used to describe the malignant status of the peritoneal fluid determined by cytologic testing.
Valid Values: Atypical Malignant Non-Malignant Unsatisfactory unknown Not Reported

Description: Text that describes the kind of disease present in the tumor specimen as related to a specific timepoint.
Valid Values: Primary Metastasis Recurrence Other unknown Not Reported Not Allowed To Collect

Description: The best improvement achieved throughout the entire course of protocol treatment.
Valid Values: AJ-Adjuvant Therapy CPD-Clinical Progression CR-Complete Response CRU-Complete Response Unconfirmed DU-Disease Unchanged IMR-Immunoresponse IPD-Immunoprogression MR-Minimal/Marginal Response MX-Mixed Response Non-CR/Non-PD-Non-CR/Non-PD NPB-No Palliative Benefit NR-No Response PA-Palliative Therapy PB-Palliative Benefit PD-Progressive Disease PPD-Pseudoprogression PR-Partial Response PSR-Pseudoresponse RD-Responsive Disease RP-Response RPD-Radiographic Progressive Disease sCR-Stringent Complete Response SD-Stable Disease SPD-Surgical Progression TE-Too Early VGPR-Very Good Partial Response

Description: The number of mitoses identified under the microscope in tumors. The method of counting varies, according to the specific tumor examined. Usually, the mitotic count is determined based on the number of mitoses per high power field (40X) or 10 high power fields.
Extent of the distant metastasis for the cancer based on evidence obtained from clinical assessment parameters determined prior to treatment.
Valid Values: M0 M1 M1a M1b M1c MX cM0 (i+) unknown Not Reported

Description: Extent of the regional lymph node involvement for the cancer based on evidence obtained from clinical assessment parameters determined prior to treatment.
Valid Values: N0 N0 (i+) N0 (i-) N0 (mol+) N0 (mol-) N1 N1a N1b N1bI N1bII N1bIII N1bIV N1c N1mi N2 N2a N2b N2c N3 N3a N3b N3c N4 NX unknown Not Reported

Description: Stage group determined from clinical information on the tumor (T), regional node (N) and metastases (M) and by grouping cases with similar prognosis for cancer.
Valid Values: Stage 0 Stage 0a Stage 0is Stage I Stage IA Stage IA1 Stage IA2 Stage IB Stage IB1 Stage IB2 Stage IC Stage II Stage IIA Stage IIA1 Stage IIA2 Stage IIB Stage IIC Stage IIC1 Stage III Stage IIIA Stage IIIB Stage IIIC Stage IIIC1 Stage IIIC2 Stage IS Stage IV Stage IVA Stage IVB Stage IVC Stage Tis Stage X unknown Not Reported

Description: Extent of the primary cancer based on evidence obtained from clinical assessment parameters determined prior to treatment.
Valid Values: T0 T1 T1a T1a1 T1a2 T1b T1b1 T1b2 T1c T1mi T2 T2a T2a1 T2a2 T2b T2c T2d T3 T3a T3b T3c T3d T4 T4a T4b T4c T4d T4e TX Ta Tis Tis (DCIS) Tis (LCIS) Tis (Paget's) unknown Not Reported

Description: Code to represent the defined absence or presence of distant spread or metastases (M) to locations via vascular channels or lymphatics beyond the regional lymph nodes, using criteria established by the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC).
Valid Values: M0 M1 M1a M1b M1c MX cM0 (i+) unknown Not Reported

Description: The codes that represent the stage of cancer based on the nodes present (N stage) according to criteria based on multiple editions of the AJCC's Cancer Staging Manual.
Valid Values: N0 N0 (i+) N0 (i-) N0 (mol+) N0 (mol-) N1 N1a N1b N1bI N1bII N1bIII N1bIV N1c N1mi N2 N2a N2b N2c N3 N3a N3b N3c N4 NX unknown Not Reported

Description: The extent of a cancer, especially whether the disease has spread from the original site to other parts of the body based on AJCC staging criteria.
Valid Values: Stage 0 Stage 0a Stage 0is Stage I Stage IA Stage IA1 Stage IA2 Stage IB Stage IB1 Stage IB2 Stage IC Stage II Stage IIA Stage IIA1 Stage IIA2 Stage IIB Stage IIC Stage IIC1 Stage III Stage IIIA Stage IIIB Stage IIIC Stage IIIC1 Stage IIIC2 Stage IS Stage IV Stage IVA Stage IVB Stage IVC Stage Tis Stage X unknown Not Reported

Description: Code of pathological T (primary tumor) to define the size or contiguous extension of the primary tumor (T), using staging criteria from the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC).
Valid Values: T0 T1 T1a T1a1 T1a2 T1b T1b1 T1b2 T1c T1mi T2 T2a T2a1 T2a2 T2b T2c T2d T3 T3a T3b T3c T3d T4 T4a T4b T4c T4d T4e TX Ta Tis Tis (DCIS) Tis (LCIS) Tis (Paget's) unknown Not Reported

Description: The text term used to describe the version or edition of the American Joint Committee on Cancer Staging Handbooks, a publication by the group formed for the purpose of developing a system of staging for cancer that is acceptable to the American medical profession and is compatible with other accepted classifications.
Valid Values: 1st 2nd 3rd 4th 5th 6th 7th 8th unknown Not Reported

Description: Text term that represents the categorization of patients on the basis of prognostic factors per a system developed by Children's Oncology Group (COG). Risk level is used to assign treatment intensity.
Valid Values: High Risk Intermediate Risk Low Risk unknown Not Reported

Description: Text term used to describe the classification of rhabdomyosarcoma, as defined by the Children's Oncology Group (COG).
Valid Values: High Risk Intermediate Risk Low Risk unknown Not Reported

Description: The text term used to describe the overall grouping of grades defined by the Gleason grading classification, which is used to determine the aggressiveness of prostate cancer. Note that this grade describes the entire prostatectomy specimen and is not specific to the sample used for sequencing.
Valid Values: Group 1 Group 2 Group 3 Group 4 Group 5

Description: The text term used to describe the tertiary pattern as described by the Gleason Grading System.
Valid Values: Pattern 4 Pattern 5

Description: Numeric value that represents the percentage of Patterns 4 and 5, which is used when the Gleason score is greater than 7 to predict prognosis.
Numeric value that represents the measurement of the widest portion of the tumor in centimeters.
The text term used to describe the International Germ Cell Cancer Collaborative Group (IGCCCG), a grouping used to further classify metastatic testicular tumors.
Valid Values: Good Prognosis Intermediate Prognosis Poor Prognosis unknown Not Reported

Description: Text term used to describe the classification of neuroblastic differentiation within neuroblastoma tumors, as defined by the International Neuroblastoma Pathology Classification (INPC).
Valid Values: Differentiating Poorly Differentiated Undifferentiated unknown Not Reported

Description: The text term used to describe the classification of neuroblastomas distinguishing between favorable and unfavorable histologic groups. The histologic score, defined by the International Neuroblastoma Pathology Classification (INPC), is based on age, mitosis-karyorrhexis index (MKI), stromal content and degree of tumor cell differentiation.
Valid Values: Favorable Unfavorable unknown Not Reported

Description: The text term used to describe the staging classification of neuroblastic tumors, as defined by the International Neuroblastoma Risk Group (INRG).
Valid Values: L1 L2 M Ms unknown Not Reported

Description: Text term used to describe the staging classification of neuroblastic tumors, as defined by the International Neuroblastoma Staging System (INSS).
Valid Values: Stage 1 Stage 2A Stage 2B Stage 3 Stage 4 Stage 4S unknown Not Reported

Description: The text term used to describe the International Prognostic Index, which classifies the prognosis of patients with aggressive non-Hodgkin's lymphoma.
Valid Values: Low Risk Low-Intermediate Risk High-Intermediate Risk High Risk

Description: Text term used to describe the classification of rhabdomyosarcoma tumors, as defined by the Intergroup Rhabdomyosarcoma Study (IRS).
Valid Values: Group I Group Ia Group Ib Group II Group IIa Group IIc Group III Group IIIa Group IIIb Group IV unknown Not Reported

Description: The text term used to describe the classification of rhabdomyosarcoma tumors, as defined by the Intergroup Rhabdomyosarcoma Study (IRS).
Valid Values: 1 2 3 4 unknown Not Reported

Description: The multiple myeloma disease stage at diagnosis.
Valid Values: I II III Not Reported unknown

Description: The text term used to describe the anatomic site of lymph node involvement.
Valid Values: Axillary Cervical Epitrochlear Femoral Hilar Iliac-common Iliac-external Iliac NOS Inguinal Mediastinal Mesenteric None Occipital Paraaortic Parotid Popliteal Retroperitoneal Splenic Submandibular Supraclavicular unknown Not Reported

Description: Numeric value (in centimeters) that represents the distance between the tumor and the surgical margin.
The text term used to describe the anatomic sites that were involved in the survival margins.
Valid Values: Gerota Fascia Parenchyma Perinephric Fat Renal Renal Capsule Renal Sinus Renal Vein Ureter

Description: The text term used to describe the classification of medulloblastoma tumors based on molecular features.
Valid Values: Not Determined Non-WNT/non-SHH Activated SHH-Activated WNT-Activated unknown Not Reported

Description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether micropapillary features were determined to be present.
Valid Values: Absent Present unknown Not Reported

Description: Text term that represents the component of the International Neuroblastoma Pathology Classification (INPC) for mitosis-karyorrhexis index (MKI).
Valid Values: High Intermediate Low unknown Not Reported

Description: The text term used to describe whether the patient had non-nodal regional disease.
Valid Values: Absent Indeterminate Present unknown Not Reported

Description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe the presence of tumor deposits in the pericolic or perirectal fat or in adjacent mesentery away from the leading edge of the tumor.
Valid Values: yes no unknown Not Reported

Description: The text term used to describe the physical condition of the involved ovary.
Valid Values: Ovarian Capsule Intact Ovarian Capsule Ruptured Ovarian Capsule Fragmented unknown Not Reported

Description: The text term that describes whether the surface tissue (outer boundary) of the ovary shows evidence of involvement or presence of cancer.
Valid Values: Absent Present Indeterminate unknown Not Reported

Description: The text term used to indicate whether the patient was pregnant at the time they were diagnosed.
Valid Values: yes no unknown Not Reported

Description: The text term used to describe the primary Gleason score, which describes the pattern of cells making up the largest area of the tumor. The primary and secondary Gleason pattern grades are combined to determine the patient's Gleason grade group, which is used to determine the aggresiveness of prostate cancer. Note that this grade describes the entire prostatectomy specimen and is not specific to the sample used for sequencing.
Valid Values: Pattern 1 Pattern 2 Pattern 3 Pattern 4 Pattern 5

Description: The text term used to describe the secondary Gleason score, which describes the pattern of cells making up the second largest area of the tumor. The primary and secondary Gleason pattern grades are combined to determine the patient's Gleason grade group, which is used to determine the aggresiveness of prostate cancer. Note that this grade describes the entire prostatectomy specimen and is not specific to the sample used for sequencing.
Valid Values: Pattern 1 Pattern 2 Pattern 3 Pattern 4 Pattern 5

Description: Text term to specify the location of the supratentorial tumor.
Valid Values: Cerebral Cortex Deep Gray Spinal Cord White Matter unknown Not Reported

Description: Numeric value that represents the depth of tumor invasion, measured in millimeters (mm).
WHO CNS Grade
Valid Values: Grade I Grade II Grade III Grade IV Grade Not Assigned unknown Not Reported

Description: WHO NTE Grade
Valid Values: G1 G2 G3 GX unknown Not Reported

Description: Numeric count of sentinel lymph nodes.

The number or amount of metastatic neoplasms related to the confirmed presence of disease or specific microorganisms during examination of the first rounded mass of lymphatic tissue to which cancer is likely to spread from the primary tumor.
The indicator to determine extranodal involvement or extent of the disease.
Valid Values: Absent Indeterminate NO YES No source documentation Not applicable Not sampled or dissected Present Present - extensive Present - minimal UNKNOWN Unspecified

Description: A yes/no indicator to ask if intransit metastases or satellite lesions are present.
Valid Values: yes no unknown

Description: A description of the location on or within the human body where the surgical biopsy/resection procedure was performed (Not covered under HTAN Clinical Data Tier 1)
The degree to which the lesion has been cut out, or resected.
Valid Values: Gross Total Resection Open Biopsy Subtotal Resection Extensive Subtotal Minor Optimal debulking Other Partial debulking Segmental Suboptimal Suboptimal debulking NTR unknown Not Reported Not Applicable

Description: Text term used to describe the mode of cancer detection, like standard of care screening or random detection
Valid Values: Standard of Care Screening Clinical Examination of unrelated cancer symptoms Incidentaloma Interval Cancer Data not available

Description: The primary tumor site used to calculate the incidence rate using the NCI Cancer Atlas, a digital atlas which provides geographical data related to cancer utilizing the Surveillance, Epidemiology, and End Results (SEER) Program cancer incidence rates for 2013 to 2017
Valid Values: Bladder Brain And Other Nervous System Female Breast In situ Female Breast Cervix Uteri Less Than Age Malignant Childhood Neoplasm Colon And Rectum Esophagus Kidney And Renal Pelvis Leukemia Liver And Bile Duct Lung And Bronchus Cutaneous Melanoma Non-Hodgkin's Lymphoma Oral Cavity And Pharynx Ovary Pancreas Prostate Gland Stomach Thyroid Gland Uterus

Description: Indicates anaplasia is present
Indicates venous invasion was detected by surgery or presence in a tumor specimen
